// Macro definitions for compact models
// Version 1.3.0-beta, March 2015
//
// Note: This file contains only macro definitions (`define) and no module definition.
// It is an include file that provides common macros used across compact models.
// Cannot be directly translated to PHDL as it contains no module.

/*
This file contains macro definitions:
- Physical constants (KELVINCONVERSION, KBOL, QELE, HBAR, MELE, EPSSI, EPSOX, etc.)
- Mathematical constants (oneSixth, oneThird, sqrtTwo, etc.)
- Clipping macros (CLIPL0p1, CLIPU0p1, CLIPB0p1, etc.)
- MAX/MIN/CLAMP macros
- Parameter declaration macros (MPRcc, MPRco, MPIcc, etc.)
- Operating point macros (OPP, OPM, OPD)

This is an include file, not a standalone module.
To use these macros, they would need to be converted to PHDL functions/constants.
*/